$ SAS programming - macro statement: %if
@ %if

{ %if %then

  gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/statements/if/then.sas||

}
{ %if %then %else

  gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/statements/if/else.sas||

}
{ %if %then %else %if %then

  gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/statements/if/if_else-if_else.sas||

}

{ %if %then %do

  gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/statements/if/then-do_else-do.sas||

}
{ Integer arithmetic via %eval #if-integer-arithmetic

  The `%if` statement uses the → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/macros/functions/eval[`%eval`] function
  to evaluate its condition.

  Since `%eval` is only capable of integer arithmetic, an `%if` statement cannot handle something like `%if 5.3 + 2.1 > 4.9`:
  gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/statements/if/integer-arithmetic.sas||

}
{ OR is possible

  Alhtough `%if` uses `%eval`, it can handle `or` conditions:
  gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/statements/if/or.sas||

}

